nt/uploads/2020/12/venushost_300-150x150.png.webp 150w\" data-was-processed=\"true\"></a></p><p><a href=\"https://www.thevenushost.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Venus Web Solutions</a> emerged during 2020 as a shared hosting provider here on LowEndBox.&nbsp;&nbsp;They started posting LEB offers <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/venus-web-solutions-shared-web-hosting-plan-or-2-37-month/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">back in August</a> and were part of our <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/venus-web-solutions-black-friday-offer-unlimited-bandwidth-shared-for-2-43-mo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Black Friday/Cyber Monday festivities</a>, then returned with a <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/the-venus-host-returns-with-a-special-full-featured-shared-hosting-offer-2-41-mo-paid-monthly/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">new offer in December</a>.</p><p class=\"p1\">\ud83c\uddee\ud83c\uddf3 This sale honors <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Republic_Day_(India)\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Republic Day</a> in India.&nbsp; That\u2019s the day (January 26) in India where the Indian Constitution came into effect back in 1950. \ud83c\uddee\ud83c\uddf3</p><p>They are again offering&nbsp;<strong>monthly</strong> pricing on their offer \u2013 no annual prepay required!&nbsp; I\u2019m always impressed by that because it means the provider is going to earn your business every month and they have confidence in their ability to do so.</p><p>I also would like to share with you the first \u201ccompetitor comparison\u201d chart I\u2019ve seen a provider submit here.&nbsp; Keep in mind this is their comparison/sales pitch, but it highlights some things <em>they</em> feel sets them apart:</p><table style=\"padding: 10px;\" border=\"1\"><thead><tr><td></td><td><b>The Venus Host</b></td><td><b>Other Hosting Providers</b></td></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><b>Bandwidth</b></td><td><p style=\"text-align: cent